This code branch includes additions to support the CESM2, UKESM and MITgcm-based models on Archer2.
Documentation is in this GitHub wiki.

This branch includes the code and simple demonstration of the use of OptClim2
Warning: This code is research quality and probably not yet suitable for production without support from those who have developed it.
All code is available on a GPLv3 license. See License.
 
 The following arre related repositories:
 - https://github.com/SimonTett/OptClim_UKESM : an example under development of using OptCLim2 with UKESM.... for real science!
 - https://github.com/Climate-Particle-Filtering : CLiamte Particle Filtering -  related develoment that has taken wings and flown to its own nest.
 
 In addition: code for an in-development OptClim3 which is not yet running on ARCHER2 or with climate models - a foundation for future work is at:
    - https://github.com/optclim/ObjectiveFunction-server
    -  https://github.com/optclim/ObjectiveFunction-client
    -  https://github.com/optclim/ModelOptimisation2
    - https://github.com/optclim/DummyModel
 
 


